"title": "1346: covenants, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1346: covenants, nature of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A solemn agreement or promise, sometimes confirmed by sacrifice or by sharing in a meal, by which two or more parties commit themselves to the rights and responsibilities demanded by their relationship and their agreed course of action, and accept the serious consequences of breaking faith.</p>\n<h2>Kinds of covenant relationship</h2>\n<h3>The relationship between king and people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3\">2SA 5:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:3\">1CH 11:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:21\">2SA 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:17\">2KI 11:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:3\">2CH 23:3</a></p>\n<h3>Terms for peace granted to a weaker party</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:15\">JOS 9:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:1\">1SA 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:19-1Kgs15:20\">1KI 15:19–15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:34\">1KI 20:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:13-Ezek17:14\">EZK 17:13–17:14</a></p>\n<h3>A mutual commitment to peaceful relations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:12\">1KI 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:27\">GEN 21:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:28-Gen26:29\">GEN 26:28–26:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:44\">GEN 31:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:9\">AMO 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>An agreement on a common course of action</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:8\">JER 34:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:4\">2KI 11:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:1\">2CH 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:3\">EZR 10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:38\">NEH 9:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:5\">PSA 83:5</a></p>\n<h3>The relationship between husband and wife</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:17\">PRO 2:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14\">MAL 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:2\">JER 2:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a></p>\n<h3>An expression of friendship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:3\">1SA 18:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:16-1Sam20:17\">1SA 20:16–20:17</a></p>\n<h2>Sealing a covenant</h2>\n<h3>By sharing a meal</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:30\">GEN 26:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:53-Gen31:54\">GEN 31:53–31:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:29\">MAT 26:26–26:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:25\">MRK 14:22–14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:17-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:17–22:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:23–11:25</a></p>\n<h3>By offering a sacrifice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:18-Jer34:19\">JER 34:18–34:19</a> <em>The Hebrew expression for making a covenant means, literally, “to cut a covenant”. This may refer to the solemn practice, described here, of cutting an animal in half and walking between its pieces</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:9-Gen15:18\">GEN 15:9–15:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4-Exod24:8\">EXO 24:4–24:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:5\">PSA 50:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a> <em>Sacrifice is an important part in sealing covenants made by God.</em></p>\n<h3>By making an oath</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:31\">GEN 21:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:31\">GEN 26:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:15\">JOS 9:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:4\">2KI 11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:28-Neh10:29\">NEH 10:28–10:29</a></p>\n<h2>The obligations of a covenant</h2>\n<h3>Covenant responsibilities must be honoured</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:2\">NUM 30:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:8\">1SA 20:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:18\">JOS 9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:33-Matt5:37\">MAT 5:33–5:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:15\">GAL 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Covenant obligations are watched over by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:42\">1SA 20:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:48-Gen31:54\">GEN 31:48–31:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:19\">JOS 9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:15-Jer34:16\">JER 34:15–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14-Mal2:16\">MAL 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>The consequences of breaking covenant faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:20\">JOS 9:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:18-Jer34:22\">JER 34:18–34:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:16-Ezek17:18\">EZK 17:16–17:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:9\">AMO 1:9</a></p>\n<h2>Covenants with other nations are forbidden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:12\">EXO 34:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:6\">DEU 23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:7\">JOS 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Covenants with other nations lead to a commitment to foreign gods</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:32-Exod23:33\">EXO 23:32–23:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:15-Exod34:16\">EXO 34:15–34:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:2-Deut7:4\">DEU 7:2–7:4</a></p>\n<h3>Covenants with other nations lead to a denial of faith in God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:15\">ISA 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:18\">ISA 28:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:1\">HOS 12:1</a></p>",
